  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Training program for medical and scientific illustrators formally operating from 1964 to 2004, but in existence from the 1920s at the University of Michigan. Various techniques were taught and used including pen and ink and carbon dust.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Original artwork (670 illustrations) by 35 different illustrators including Gerald P. Hodge, Alfred Teoli, Evelyn Erickson Sullivan, Emily Perry, Max Brödel, Jeanette Young and Ralph Sweet. Most illustrations depict surgical techniques and anatomical drawings. Also audio-visual instructional material and presentations in various formats including 16 mm film; U-matic and VHS videotapes, and slides.</subfield>
  </datafield>
